      "commit": {
        "parents": [
          {
            "commit": "e3ae2055f629c9bfea32905cd44e22c692cd65d9",
            "subject": "LU-9008 pfl: Read should not trigger layout write intent"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Bobi Jam",
          "email": "bobijam.xu@intel.com",
          "date": "2017-04-10 17:50:04.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Jinshan Xiong",
          "email": "jinshan.xiong@intel.com",
          "date": "2017-04-18 03:13:54.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-9311 pfl: shouldn't reprocess granted resent request",
        "message": "LU-9311 pfl: shouldn't reprocess granted resent request\n\nWhen the LOVEA buffer is bigger than the request reply buffer, the\nclient will resend the layout write intent RPC, and\nmdt_layout_change() should not reprocess it since the 2nd process\nwill try to cancel the 1st granted CR lock, while client has not\nget it granted yet because of the reply buffer shortage resend the\nRPC.\n\nThis patch also adjusts some debug messages, makes dump_lsm() dump\nuninstantiated component stripe info.\n\nSigned-off-by: Bobi Jam <bobijam.xu@intel.com>\nChange-Id: If64531c53ab494c785ad11b4f71fd0f1b562d47d\nReviewed-on: https://review.whamcloud.com/26612\nTested-by: Jenkins\nReviewed-by: Bobi Jam <bobijam@hotmail.com>\nTested-by: Maloo <hpdd-maloo@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Emoly Liu <emoly.liu@intel.com>\nTested-by: Emoly Liu <emoly.liu@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Jinshan Xiong <jinshan.xiong@intel.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/pfl"
    }
  },
